newsitem.title: USA: CBOT overnight Project A ag volume 765 contracts.
newsitem.headline: CBOT overnight Project A ag volume 765 contracts.

text.p: Chicago Board of Trade's Project A overnight agricultural contracts trading volume totaled 765 contracts, according to the CBOT.
There were 178 wheat contracts, 174 corn, 334 soybean, 43 soymeal and 36 soyoil futures contracts traded, along with 6 corn call and 6 soybean call options.

The overnight trend for corn was 1-1/2 cent lower to 1-3/4 cents per bushel lower, soybeans 3/4 to one cent lower, wheat 3/4 to 2-1/4 cents lower, soymeal 20 cents higher to 60 cents per ton lower, and soyoil 0.07 cent per lb higher.
